The article discusses the Trump administration's response to recent events in Hong Kong and its criticism of China's actions. It mentions that the administration declared the death of Hong Kong's free society in May 2020, and highlights the recent arrests of over 50 people, including former elected officials, as a further blow to Hong Kong's democracy. The article also mentions the administration's demand for answers from Beijing regarding the origins of the virus and its accusation that the World Health Organization enabled a cover-up by deferring to the Chinese Communist Party. It emphasizes the need for accountability from Beijing and states that the United States is considering further options to respond.